climbs.name: Swedish Cleaning Lady
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Tobias, Suzette Olsen, Andrea Tomaszewski, Karen Miller, Laurell Collela, Shelly Herndon, Matt, Tucker Tech

content.description:
Boulder out some insecure moves to a high first bolt (easier to the left) and then pull over a small overlap via some nice edges. Continue up interesting face past one more bolt and finish direct or somewhat to the right.

Belay from a bolted anchor but rap off the lower anchor (the one for Onatopp and Moneypenny) if you want to get your rope back (hint, hint).
content.location:
Located on the far right side of the north face, about 20' right of

Onatopp

.

content.description: This is the slightly overhanging OWth crack on a small formation directly across from the N. Face of the spire.
content.protection: trad gear;  med, large, and XL.
content.location: Safe Zone Area of Indian Head.

content.description: Starts with opposing sidepulls and a difficult reach to small edges before pulling onto the slab above. Once past the crux wander up the face above staying between the two bolted routes.
content.location: Located on the face between Moneypenny and Onatopp.

climbs.name: Onatopp
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Kistle Lund, Cyndie Bransford

content.description:
Climb vertical face with big holds onto the shoulder of the east face and then work your way left and then back right on a featured steep slab passing a horizontal crack (2.5"-3" piece) about two-thirds of the way up. Finish up a short section of slab to a shared anchor with Moneypenny.

If climbing at or near the grade a piece of gear in the horizontal is nice, otherwise you can climb it like a sport route with quickdraws only.
content.protection: 4 bolts, 2.5" or 3" piece. The anchor/rap consists of a fixed pin/single bolt.
content.location:
Located on the rounded left side of the north face, around and right from

Moneypenny

and starting off a block.

climbs.name: Moneypenny
climbs.fa: Todd Gordon, Cyndie Bransford, Kestle Lund

content.description: Make you way carefully to the base and then make a reach to clip the first bolt (easier if tall). Power over the somewhat reachy and technical roof to a ledge and then slab your way to the top past two more bolts and a couple of small-sized gear placements.
content.location: Left side of the east face (the one you see on the approach) and starts with a small roof above a sloping slab.

content.description:
Scramble up ledges to reach this obvious right-slanting thin to hands crack that ends on the shoulder and then joins

Moneypenny

as it continues up the face past one bolt to anchors atop the formation.
content.protection:
Gear to 2.5 inches, 1 bolt

Bolted anchor/rap
content.location: Located on the south face of the formation.

content.description: There is an easy route up the backside of this spire. I believe it is about 5.5, and the protection isn't all that good.
content.protection: A few pieces, if you can get them...Probably small to med.
content.location: Back side of the spire in the Safezone area of Indian Head.
